The paper addresses unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a method that involves learning to perform auxiliary self-supervised tasks on both domains simultaneously to align the learned representations of the source and target domains while preserving discriminability. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
